SUMMARY:Hamilton Waterfall & Brewery Tour
DESCRIPTION:Wilderness Union Toronto - Outdoor Adventure and Hiking Club\n
 **Please note the only way to register for this adventure is on [our websi
 te.](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/hamilton-winter-2026)**\n\
 n***Hamilton’s nature is a well-kept secret\, as the city contains the m
 ost waterfalls of any city in the world! We hear their beer is pretty good
  too…***\n\nFor this adventure we're combining a hike with a mini food t
 our. First\, we'll hike to the falls: This easy 8km hike will take us on a
  beautiful loop through the Dundas Valley Conservation Area\, and passing 
 by Canterbury and Sherman falls. The hike crosses the Bruce Trail as we ma
 ke our way through the Niagara Escarpment\, so we'll be going through\, ov
 er or around fields\, forests\, orchards and plenty of streams.\n\nOnce we
  finish hiking\, we’ll head into town and drop in for a pint and some lu
 nch at Merit craft brewery. There'll be non-alcoholic options available ma
 king it suitable for all members.\n\n**Please note that self-drivers will 
 need to pay for parking both at the trailhead and in town\, which totals a
 round $15. We recommend joining us on the bus to save on costs and hassle!
 **\n\n**Depending on snow levels we may be required to use snowshoes or ic
 e spikes. We have a limited quantity available that you can grab at check-
 out. Ice spikes are free to borrow and snow shoes can be rented for a smal
 l fee.**\n\n**Highlights**\n**Waterfalls**: Explore the Waterfall Capital 
 where stunning cascades are around every corner\n**Craft Beer**: Wrap up t
 he day with a refreshing craft beer at Merit Brewery\, local favourites kn
 own for quality brews and welcoming vibes.\n**Incredible Hamilton Nature**
 : Check out lesser-known nature spots just down the road from Toronto.\n\n
 **Event cost: $50+HST - optional transport available.**\n**Register [here.
 ](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/hamilton-winter-2026)**\n\n**
 About Wilderness Union**\nWilderness Union is deliberate about building an
  outdoors community that connects you to the life-changing magic of the ou
 tdoors and helps you find your people.\n\nMembers range from 20-40 years o
 ld. The group is a mix of GTA locals and newcomers to Toronto from within 
 Canada and abroad.\n\nAttendance numbers on Meetup don't reflect our actua
 l event attendance - we typically have 15-20 community members at each eve
 nt. Large enough that there's someone new to meet but small enough that it
 's not overwhelming!\n\n***Learn more at our website [www.wildernessunion.
 com](https://www.wildernessunion.com/)***
